# Custom Theme System — Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal `light / dark / system` toggle stored at `t3code:theme` in localStorage. The request is to replace this with a richer **named theme system** featuring 3 built-in colour palettes (`t3-dark`, `t3-light`, `t3-midnight`), each covering 7 semantic colour areas (background, foreground, accent, sidebar, editor, terminal, status bar). The theme type lives in the shared package, a provider + hook live in the web app, and a selector component with visual swatches replaces the existing radio buttons in the Settings page.

**Constraints:**
- Do NOT modify build configuration or add new dependencies.
- `bun lint` and `bun typecheck` must pass.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` | **NEW** — theme types + 3 built-in definitions |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | Add `./theme` subpath export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` | **REWRITE** — named-theme external store |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` | **NEW** — provider component |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **NEW** — selector with swatches |
| `apps/web/src/router.ts` | Mount `ThemeProvider` in `Wrap` |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | Replace theme UI with `<ThemeSelector />` |

Files that do **not** change: `index.css`, `packages/contracts/`, build configs, vite configs.

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (new file)

Pure TypeScript; zero dependencies (no Effect, no contracts). Follows the same standalone file pattern as `packages/shared/src/git.ts`.

```ts
/** Identifier for a built-in colour theme. */
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

/** The 7 semantic colour tokens every theme must define. Values are CSS colour strings. */
export interface ThemeColorTokens {
  /** Main app background */
  background: string;
  /** Primary text colour */
  foreground: string;
  /** Interactive accent / primary colour */
  accent: string;
  /** Sidebar panel background */
  sidebar: string;
  /** Code-editor area background */
  editor: string;
  /** Terminal area background */
  terminal: string;
  /** Status-bar background */
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface ThemeDefinition {
  readonly id: ThemeId;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly isDark: boolean;
  readonly colors: ThemeColorTokens;
}
```

**Built-in themes** (concrete colour values):

| Token | t3-light | t3-dark | t3-midnight |
|---|---|---|---|
| background | `#ffffff` | `#0f0f0f` | `#0d0015` |
| foreground | `#1a1a1a` | `#ededed` | `#e8dff5` |
| accent | `oklch(0.488 0.217 264)` | `oklch(0.588 0.217 264)` | `oklch(0.65 0.27 288)` |
| sidebar | `#f4f4f5` | `#161616` | `#110020` |
| editor | `#fafafa` | `#0d0d0d` | `#08000d` |
| terminal | `#f0f0f0` | `#141414` | `#0f001a` |
| statusBar | `#e4e4e7` | `#0a0a0a` | `#0a0016` |
| isDark | false | true | true |

Also export:
- `const T3_DARK_THEME: ThemeDefinition` — the first (default) entry, as a named `const` to avoid index-access issues with `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`
- `const BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly ThemeDefinition[]`
- `const DEFAULT_THEME_ID: ThemeId = "t3-dark"`
- `function getThemeById(id: ThemeId): ThemeDefinition` — returns definition or falls back to `T3_DARK_THEME`

---

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json`

Add one entry to the `exports` object (identical pattern to the existing entries):

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

---

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (rewrite)

**Remove:** `"light" | "dark" | "system"` type, `systemDark` snapshot field, `window.matchMedia` listener.

**Add:** Import from `@t3tools/shared/theme`.

Key implementation points:

```ts
import { type ThemeId, BUILT_IN_THEMES, DEFAULT_THEME_ID, getThemeById } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";

const STORAGE_KEY = "t3code:theme";  // same key; old values migrate gracefully

function getStored(): ThemeId {
  const raw = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
  if (raw === "t3-dark" || raw === "t3-light" || raw === "t3-midnight") return raw;
  // Migrate legacy values
  if (raw === "light") return "t3-light";
  // "dark" | "system" | null | unknown → default
  return DEFAULT_THEME_ID;
}

function applyTheme(themeId: ThemeId, suppressTransitions = false) {
  const theme = getThemeById(themeId);
  const el = document.documentElement;

  if (suppressTransitions) el.classList.add("no-transitions");

  // Toggle .dark class (drives existing Tailwind dark: utilities and CSS @variant dark)
  el.classList.toggle("dark", theme.isDark);
  // Update color-scheme for browser chrome (scrollbars, inputs)
  el.style.colorScheme = theme.isDark ? "dark" : "light";

  // Override the 7 semantic tokens via inline style (highest CSS specificity)
  el.style.setProperty("--background", theme.colors.background);
  el.style.setProperty("--foreground", theme.colors.foreground);
  el.style.setProperty("--primary",    theme.colors.accent);
  el.style.setProperty("--ring",       theme.colors.accent);
  el.style.setProperty("--sidebar",             theme.colors.sidebar);
  el.style.setProperty("--editor-background",   theme.colors.editor);
  el.style.setProperty("--terminal-background", theme.colors.terminal);
  el.style.setProperty("--status-bar",          theme.colors.statusBar);

  if (suppressTransitions) {
    // oxlint-disable-next-line no-unused-expressions
    el.offsetHeight;  // force reflow
    requestAnimationFrame(() => el.classList.remove("no-transitions"));
  }
}

// Apply immediately on module load to prevent flash
applyTheme(getStored());
```

`getSnapshot` returns `{ themeId: ThemeId }`.  
`subscribe` only listens to `storage` events (no media query — no "system" mode).

`useTheme()` export:
```ts
export function useTheme() {
  const snapshot = useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot);
  const themeId = snapshot.themeId;
  const theme = getThemeById(themeId);
  const resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark" = theme.isDark ? "dark" : "light";

  const setTheme = useCallback((next: ThemeId) => {
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, next);
    applyTheme(next, true);
    emitChange();
  }, []);

  // Keep DOM in sync on mount/change
  useEffect(() => { applyTheme(themeId); }, [themeId]);

  return { themeId, theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme } as const;
}
```

Note: `BUILT_IN_THEMES` is re-exported from the hook so consumers can iterate without a separate import.

---

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` (new file)

A thin mounting component that ensures the theme is active at the root of the component tree and provides a clear semantic anchor for the system.

```tsx
import type { ReactNode } from "react";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

interface ThemeProviderProps {
  children: ReactNode;
}

/** Mounts the named-theme system. Place at the root of the component tree. */
export function ThemeProvider({ children }: ThemeProviderProps) {
  // Calling useTheme() here ensures the external-store subscription is active
  // at the root level and the useEffect keeps the DOM in sync on changes.
  useTheme();
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

---

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (new file)

Renders a radio-group of theme buttons. Each button contains a `ThemeSwatch` — a 72×48 px mini-preview built entirely with inline styles (no new CSS classes needed).

Swatch layout (illustrative):
```
┌──────────────────────┐
│sidebar│ ──────────── │  ← foreground lines (0.6 / 0.3 opacity)
│ strip │              │
│       │          ●   │  ← accent dot
│       ├──────────────│
│       │  status bar  │
└──────────────────────┘
```

```tsx
import { BUILT_IN_THEMES, type ThemeColorTokens, type ThemeDefinition } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { themeId, setTheme } = useTheme();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Colour theme">
      {BUILT_IN_THEMES.map((theme) => {
        const selected = themeId === theme.id;
        return (
          <button
            key={theme.id}
            type="button"
            role="radio"
            aria-checked={selected}
            onClick={() => setTheme(theme.id)}
            className={`flex w-full items-center gap-4 rounded-lg border px-3 py-2.5 text-left transition-colors ${
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground"
                : "border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent"
            }`}
          >
            <ThemeSwatch colors={theme.colors} selected={selected} />
            <span className="flex flex-1 flex-col">
              <span className="text-sm font-medium">{theme.name}</span>
            </span>
            {selected && (
              <span className="rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                Active
              </span>
            )}
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}

function ThemeSwatch({ colors, selected }: { colors: ThemeColorTokens; selected: boolean }) {
  return (
    <div
      aria-hidden="true"
      className={`relative shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-md border-2 transition-colors ${
        selected ? "border-primary/50" : "border-border/50"
      }`}
      style={{ width: 72, height: 48, background: colors.background }}
    >
      {/* Sidebar strip */}
      <div style={{ position: "absolute", left: 0, top: 0, width: "22%", height: "80%", background: colors.sidebar }} />
      {/* Foreground text lines */}
      <div style={{ position: "absolute", left: "28%", top: "22%", width: "50%", height: 2, borderRadius: 1, background: colors.foreground, opacity: 0.6 }} />
      <div style={{ position: "absolute", left: "28%", top: "42%", width: "38%", height: 2, borderRadius: 1, background: colors.foreground, opacity: 0.3 }} />
      {/* Accent dot */}
      <div style={{ position: "absolute", right: "8%", bottom: "22%", width: 6, height: 6, borderRadius: "50%", background: colors.accent }} />
      {/* Status bar strip */}
      <div style={{ position: "absolute", left: 0, right: 0, bottom: 0, height: "18%", background: colors.statusBar }} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

### Step 6 — `apps/web/src/router.ts`

Add `ThemeProvider` to the `Wrap` function (wrap innermost — inside `StoreProvider`):

```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "./components/ThemeProvider";

Wrap: ({ children }) =>
  createElement(
    QueryClientProvider,
    { client: queryClient },
    createElement(
      StoreProvider,
      null,
      createElement(ThemeProvider, null, children),
    ),
  ),
```

---

### Step 7 — `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

**Appearance section changes:**

1. Remove `THEME_OPTIONS` constant (no longer needed).
2. Remove `theme`, `setTheme`, `resolvedTheme` from the `useTheme()` destructure (or remove that call entirely — the `ThemeSelector` component calls `useTheme` internally).
3. Replace the `<div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" ...>` block and the "Active theme:" paragraph with:

```tsx
import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";

// Inside the Appearance section, replace the radio button block with:
<ThemeSelector />
```

The section `<h2>` and description paragraph remain unchanged.

---

## CSS Custom Property Mechanics

The `applyTheme` function sets inline styles on `document.documentElement`. Because **inline styles have the highest CSS specificity**, they override both the `:root {}` light defaults and the `@variant dark {}` dark overrides already in `index.css`. This means:

- `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--ring` are now fully theme-controlled.
- `--muted`, `--border`, `--card`, `--popover`, and the other derived tokens are **still driven by the `.dark` class** in `index.css` — no CSS changes required.
- The new tokens `--sidebar`, `--editor-background`, `--terminal-background`, `--status-bar` are set as new custom properties available for components to adopt over time.

`index.css` is **not modified**.

---

## TypeScript Safety Notes

- `packages/shared` uses `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` — avoid `BUILT_IN_THEMES[0]`; use the named `T3_DARK_THEME` const as the default fallback instead.
- `exactOptionalPropertyTypes` — all interface fields are required (non-optional) in `ThemeColorTokens` and `ThemeDefinition`.
- The `// oxlint-disable-next-line no-unused-expressions` comment pattern (already used in the existing `useTheme.ts`) is needed on the `el.offsetHeight` reflow line.
- `packages/shared`'s tsconfig has Effect language service with `importFromBarrel: "error"` — `theme.ts` makes no imports at all, so this is not an issue.

---

## Verification

After implementation, run:

```bash
bun lint       # must pass with no new errors
bun typecheck  # must pass across all workspaces
```

Manual smoke-test:
1. Open Settings → Appearance section shows three theme buttons with colour swatches.
2. Selecting each theme immediately changes the app's colours (background, text, primary colour).
3. Reload the page — selected theme persists (localStorage round-trip).
4. Open a second tab — changing the theme in one tab syncs to the other via the `storage` event handler.
5. Verify `.dark` is on `<html>` for `t3-dark` and `t3-midnight`, absent for `t3-light`.
6. Verify `document.documentElement.style.getPropertyValue("--background")` returns the expected hex value for each theme via browser devtools.

